üç™What are cookies?
Cookies are small text files saved on your device when visiting a website to remember your device and its associated preferences.
‚ùîWhy does Swapcard use cookies?
We use cookies to remember your preferences, offer you the best experience, make sure everything works properly, analyze our traffic, and gather analytics and advertising information on how you use our website.
üìùWhich cookies does Swapcard use?
The cookies we use are listed in the ‚Äòdetails‚Äô tab of the cookie preferences center. We also uses Google Analytics, which uses the information generated by cookies for its own purposes and may transfer your information outside of the EU. To learn more, click here.
‚ùåHow do I turn cookies off?
You can set your cookies preferences via our cookie banner or via the cookie widget at the bottom left corner of our website. You can also configure your browser to accept or reject cookies, which may affect your browsing experience on our website.
